        public DecisionModel​(java.lang.String modelName)

      • DecisionModel

        public DecisionModel​(java.lang.String modelName,
                     java.lang.String trackURL,
                     java.lang.String trackApiKey)
        Parameters:
        modelName - Length of modelName must be in range [1, 64]; Only alphanumeric characters([a-zA-Z0-9]), '-', '.' and '_' are allowed in the modelName and the first character must be an alphanumeric one;
        trackURL - url for tracking decisions. If trackURL is null, no decisions would be tracked. If trackURL is not a valid URL, an exception would be thrown.
        trackApiKey - will be attached to the header fields of all the post request for tracking
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if an invalid modelName or an invalid trackURL

      • loadAsync

        @Deprecated
public void loadAsync​(java.net.URL modelUrl,
                      DecisionModel.LoadListener listener)
        Deprecated.
        The callback method signature will likely have to change for multiple URLs
        Notice that it's not recommended to call this method directly in an Android Activity as it may cause leaks. Before we add a cancel method to allow aborting downloading tasks, you may have to call loadAsync() in something like a Singleton class.

      • chooseMultiVariate

        public Decision chooseMultiVariate​(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​?> variants)
        This method is an alternative of chooseFrom(). An example here might be more expressive: chooseMultiVariate({"style":["bold", "italic"], "size":[3, 5]}) is equivalent to chooseFrom([ {"style":"bold", "size":3}, {"style":"italic", "size":3}, {"style":"bold", "size":5}, {"style":"italic", "size":5}, ])
        Parameters:
        variants - Variants can be any JSON encodeable data structure of arbitrary complexity like chooseFrom(). The value of the dictionary is expected to be a List. If not, it would be treated as an one-element List anyway. So chooseMultiVariate({"style":["bold", "italic"], "size":3}) is equivalent to chooseMultiVariate({"style":["bold", "italic"], "size":[3]})
        Returns:
        An IMPDecision object.

      • which

        public java.lang.Object which​(java.lang.Object... variants)
        This is a short hand version of chooseFrom(variants).get() that returns the chosen result directly.
        Parameters:
        variants - See chooseFrom(). When the only argument is a List, it's equivalent to calling chooseFrom(variants).get(); When the only argument is a Map, it's equivalent to calling chooseMultiVariate(variants).get(); When there are two or more arguments, all the arguments would form a list and be passed to chooseFrom();
        Returns:
        Returns the chosen variant
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if variants is null or empty; or if there's only one variant and it's not a List or Map.

      • score

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Double> score​(java.util.List variants)
        If this method is called before the model is loaded, or errors occurred while loading the model file, a randomly generated list of descending Gaussian scores is returned.
        Parameters:
        variants - Variants can be any JSON encodeable data structure of arbitrary complexity, including nested maps, arrays, strings, numbers, nulls, and booleans.
        Returns:
        scores of the variants
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if variants is null or empty.

      • scoreInternal

        protected java.util.List<java.lang.Double> scoreInternal​(java.util.List variants,
                                                         java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​?> givens)
        If this method is called before the model is loaded, or errors occurred while loading the model file, a randomly generated list of descending Gaussian scores is returned.
        Parameters:
        variants - Variants can be any JSON encodeable data structure of arbitrary complexity, including nested maps, arrays, strings, numbers, nulls, and booleans.
        givens - Additional context info that will be used with each of the variants to calculate the score, including the givens passed in through DecisionModel.given(givens) and the givens provided by the AppGivensProvider or other custom GivensProvider.
        Returns:
        scores of the variants
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if variants is null or empty

      • addReward

        public void addReward​(double reward)
        This method should only be called on Android platform. Adds the reward value to the most recent Decision for this model name for this installation. The most recent Decision can be from a different DecisionModel instance or a previous session as long as they have the same model name. If no previous Decision is found, the reward will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        reward - the reward to add. Must not be NaN, or Infinity.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if `reward` is NaN or Infinity
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - Thrown if trackURL is null, or called on non-Android platform.
